This paper discusses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the properties of different latent state spaces and their connection to model-based and model-free reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses temporal difference learning, which is a common technique in reinforcement learning, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses neural networks to learn representations, which is a common technique in deep learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
